      <td valign="top" style="text-align:left;">      
        <div id="comment188791_show" class="single_comment">
          I'm really enjoying this game. I'll find myself wanting to take a second turn if I stay awake past midnight, but then feeling strangely guilty about it. I'm also learning my priorities. If something is on the map that would take several extra days to see, even if it could be nothing and has no real significance to the rest of the game, I find myself invariably going after it. Take the short and easy path, or the path with something cool on it. As of yet, I haven't come across two paths that are equally interesting, but choosing between them would be hell!<br />&#10;<br />&#10;This is the first Michael Brough I've played, but it certainly won't be my last. 
        </div>
